p: In the comparison of the three extracts, it was observed that the underestimation of the antiproliferative effect was more notable in the essential oil, which may be related to a synergic effect of some volatile compounds with antioxidant characteristics present in the extract such as eugenol, methyl eugenol and other compounds including isoborneol, eucalyptol, spathulenol, a profile of volatile compounds that have been previously identified [ 11]. The isolation of the active compounds from these extracts, as well as in vivo studies are necessary, and that can improve understanding of the mechanisms underlying these bioactivities.
